      <name>Manage data logs</name>
      <Narrative>
        <completeDescription>Via a Customer Portal, a Data Owner (e.g. electricity consumer is the owner of its consumption data) has access to data logs. They include two types of logs:&lt;br/&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Data access logs: e.g. who has accessed data and when&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Authorization logs: e.g. who has requested/received authorization to access data and when&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Authentication logs: e.g. who has identified himself/herself in Customer Portal and when&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;The Customer Portal operator makes the data logs available in the Customer Portal. In addition, in case of cross border data exchange, the Customer Portal operators of the involved countries share information about data logs between them.</completeDescription>
        <mRID>7a7f06c4-2d87-40a6-b48a-2e556d80e419</mRID>
        <shortDescription>Data Owner&amp;#8217;s access to data logs contributes to personal data protection. The data logs include information about data access (e.g. who has accessed consumption data and when), authorizations (e.g. who has issued a new authorization and when) and authentication (e.g. who has identified himself/herself in Customer Portal and when).</shortDescription>
      </Narrative>
      <nature>SUC</nature>
